  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Water &amp; Sanitation Infrastructure Masvingo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">50% of Bikita and Zaka districts&apos; rural health centres do not have access to running water, and 90% do not possess adequate sanitation facilities. The intervention, which consists of rehabilitating the water and sanitation infrastructure in four referral hospitals and 42 rural health centres, is meant to contribute to improve health delivery. It will reduce infant, child and maternal mortality, facilitate access to reproductive health services and prevent cholera and other water borne diseases related deaths.</narrative>
  </description>
